    "description": "<p>A pickaxe, pick-axe, or pick is a generally T-shaped hand tool used for prying. Its head is typically metal, attached perpendicularly to a longer handle. A standard pickaxe has a pointed end on one side of its head and a broad flat \"axe\" blade opposite. The historic pickaxe was readily adapted to a weapon for hand-to-hand combat in ancient times.</p>",
